<h2 id="editors-notes">Editor’s notes</h2>

<p>Hello my friends! In is guitar lesson, I will teach you how to play The Sound of Silence, the 1966 classic from Simon and Garfunkel. I will be using a capo on 6th fret, matching how they play it. The song uses fingerstyle in verse 1, and is strummed for verses 2-5, all of which the same chord progression. I’ll teach you everything you need to know to play it: the chord shapes, the progression, how to approach the fingerstyle (beginner &amp; advanced techniques), and a few different ways to tackle the strumming. Lastly, I it all off with a full playthrough showing you everything put together in one package.</p>

<p>￼Because this is such a classic song, I wanted to go deep and be complete – hence this one being a little bit longer than normal. But with my timestamps, I trust you’ll be able to find what you’re looking for quickly. good luck, and enjoy!￼￼</p>

<p>Video timestamps:</p>

<ul>
  <li>0:00 Song preview &amp; lesson summary</li>
  <li>3:19 Capo and chord shapes</li>
  <li>4:17 Verse basics, w/ simple strum tab</li>
  <li>7:44 Fingerstyle technique crash course</li>
  <li>11:49 Fingerstyle tab (basic)</li>
  <li>18:04 Fingerstyle tab (advanced)</li>
  <li>20:46 Strumming patterns (basic)</li>
  <li>23:04 Strumming pattern (advanced)</li>
  <li>27:41 Chord progressions</li>
  <li>29:50 Full playthrough w/ lyrics</li>
</ul>

