<h2 id="capo-and-key">Capo and key</h2>

<p>Add a capo 6th fret to play along with Simon and Garfunkel’s album version of this song.</p>

<p>Capo 6th fret  =  Key of A minor
   No Capo        =  Key D# minor (which is equal to Eb minor)</p>

<h2 id="chord-shapes-needed">Chord shapes needed</h2>

<p>Here’s how to play the five chords you’ll need in this song. The trickiest of these may be the F chord, but don’t feel like you need to play for six string barred version of F (which is often quite difficult for beginners). Instead, you can use any of the alternate voicings of the F that I show here – none of which require you to barre any of the strings.</p>

